Funny but true I ran into it while thinking I wanted to see the classic gmtime() function.  It's so funny to see how the gmtime function set's the struct tm's fields:<p><pre><code>        /*
         * generate hours:minutes:seconds
         */
        *tp++ = hms%60;
        d1 = hms/60;
        *tp++ = d1%60;
        d1 /= 60;
        *tp++ = d1;

</code></pre>
It uses a pointer and does *tp++ = value rather then p->tm_hour = XX<p>Very efficient but would be frowned upon in modern code reviews.  Sometimes I think the "art" of performance has been lost to our modern development values.
